  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The development to which this permission relates shall be commenced not later than the expiration of 3 years from the date of this permission.",
    "Condition : 2 - The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans: 01; 02; 03; 04; 05; 06; 133115/PA/004.",
    "Condition : 3 - The facing materials to be used for the development hereby permitted shall be those specified in the application form unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.",
    "Condition : 4 - No demolition or construction work or ancillary activities such as deliveries shall take place before 8am or after 6pm Mondays - Fridays inclusive, before 8am or after 1pm on Saturdays or at any time on Sundays or Bank Holidays.",
    "Condition : 5 - A preliminary risk assessment, then an investigation shall be undertaken to consider the potential for contaminated-land, and if necessary, a detailed remediation scheme to bring the site to a suitable state for the intended use by removing unacceptable risks to health and the built environment, and submitted to the approval of the LPA.  \r\n \r\nReason: To protect the health of future users of the site in accordance with policy E7, part B, section 3f of the London Plan 2021 and policy DM EP4 of Merton's sites and policies plan 2014.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "Condition : 6 - The approached remediation shall be completed prior to completion.  And a verification report, demonstrating the then effectiveness of the remediation, subject to the approval of the LPA.  \r\n\r\nReason: To protect the health of future users of the site in accordance with policy E7, part B, section 3f of the London Plan 2021 and policy DM EP4 of Merton's sites and policies plan 2014.",
    "Condition : 7 - The roof windows in the extension hereby permitted shall remain fixed shut in order to prevent dust leaving the site.\r\n\r\nReason: in the interests of air quality and neighbouring amenity, and to accord with the Environment Agencies recommendations. \r\n",
    "Condition : 8 - Prior to commencement of development above first floor level hereby permitted, the applicant shall submit to and be approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority noise insulation measures to mitigate noise impacts arising form the proposed use of the development.\r\n\r\nReason: in the interests of neighbouring amenity, and to accord with the Environment Agencies recommendations.",
    "Condition : 9 - The operation of the site shall be from 0630 to 1830 hours Monday to Saturday, with the core hours for the manufacture of aggregate, i.e. the principal noise generating activities, shall be limited to 0730 to 1730 hours Monday to Saturday. There are to be no proposed works on Sundays and Bank/Public Holidays.\r\n\r\nReason: in the interests of neighbouring amenity, and to accord with the Environment Agencies recommendations.\r\n",
    "Condition : 10 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development)(England) Order 2015 (or any order revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification), no window, door or other opening other than those expressly authorised by this permission shall be constructed in any elevation of the extension (including roof) without planning permission first being obtained from the Local Planning Authority.",
    "Condition : 11 - INFORMATIVE: A Groundwater Risk Management Permit from Thames Water will be required for discharging groundwater into a public sewer.  Any discharge made without a permit is deemed illegal and may result in prosecution under the provisions of the Water Industry Act 1991.  We would expect the developer to demonstrate what measures he will undertake to minimise groundwater discharges into the public sewer.  Permit enquiries should be directed to Thames Water's Risk Management Team by telephoning 020 3577 9483 or by emailing trade.effluent@thameswater.co.uk .  Application forms should be completed on line via www.thameswater.co.uk.  Please refer to the Wholsesale; Business customers; Groundwater discharges section.",
    "Condition : 12 - INFORMATIVE: Thames Water will aim to provide customers with a minimum pressure of 10m head (approx 1 bar) and a flow rate of 9 litres/minute at the point where it leaves Thames Waters pipes. The developer should take account of this minimum pressure in the design of the proposed development."
  ],
